<concept id="concept_3C89B4C4D3EA47DE9CB046286D26F0BC">
	<title>history</title>
	<shortdesc>Show or save the command history. </shortdesc>
	<conbody>
		<p> This history can be saved to a file which can also be used as a script later. </p>
		<p>A history of commands that have been executed successfully is also logged in
				<codeph>.gfsh.history</codeph> file in the home directory of the user running gfsh. </p>
		<p><b> Availability:</b> Online or offline. </p>
		<p><b>Syntax:</b>
			<codeblock>history [--file=&lt;history text file&gt;]</codeblock>
			<table id="table_7E667378EB6849888206A4F680F60576">
				<title>Parameters</title>
				<tgroup cols="3">
					<colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="1.00*"/>
					<colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="2.50*"/>
					<colspec colname="newCol3" colnum="3" colwidth="1*"/>
					<thead>
						<row>
							<entry colname="col1">Name </entry>
							<entry colname="col2">Description</entry>
							<entry>Default Value</entry>
						</row>
					</thead>
					<tbody>
						<row>
							<entry colname="col1">--file </entry>
							<entry colname="col2"> File to which the history is to be saved. </entry>
							<entry/>
						</row>
						<row>
							<entry colname="col1">--clear</entry>
							<entry colname="col2">When set to <codeph>true</codeph>, clears the
								history of gfsh commands. </entry>
							<entry>false</entry>
						</row>
					</tbody>
				</tgroup>
			</table>
		</p>
		<p><b>Example Commands:</b>
			<codeblock>history
history --file=./mycommands.gfsh;</codeblock>
		</p>
		<p><b>Sample Output:</b>
			<codeblock>gfsh&gt;history --file=./mycommands.gfsh
Wrote successfully to file ./mycommands.gfsh</codeblock>
		</p>
	</conbody>
</concept>
